## 7. Limitations and blockers

- Pixels are spatially autocorrelated; no inferential tests reported at pixel level.
- Reference label asymmetry between events (Yecheon Sentinel-only, Pohang log-run) — all metrics inherit this provenance.
- n = 2 events in the original FAR-filter narrative, extended to 3 in the released JSON/CSV; cross-event generalization is a working hypothesis, not a regime law.
- Probability bimodality caps the utility of quantile-based filters; a calibration pipeline is not in scope for this analysis bundle.

